  "text": "This paper assumes a lunar base sited at the South Pole near the Shackleton crater. The relatively constant thermal and illumination conditions along with the potential of water at the South Pole makes this area an attractive site for a manned lunar base. Preliminary data indicates that regions located near the Shackleton crater receive sunlight for much of the lunar day [CITATION_1] .",
